news_header: 157 killer whales stranded in Tasmania; rescue efforts are challenging due to their weight and location.
news_original_title: Why do whales and dolphins strand?
news_text: 157 killer whales are stranded on a remote beach in Tasmania. Most are alive, but rescuing them is difficult due to their weight and location. Whales often do not survive strandings. Various factors, including navigation errors and human-made noise, contribute to these incidents.
